<taxonomicName authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1897" box="[224,337,356,379]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Neaporia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="105" pageNumber="104" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[224,337,356,379]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="104">Neaporia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is also distinguished by an elytron with a unique color pattern. The 
<typeStatus box="[1213,1318,355,379]" pageId="105" pageNumber="104">holotype</typeStatus>
is labeled “V, de 
<collectingRegion box="[268,374,387,411]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="105" pageNumber="104">Chiriqui</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity box="[384,507,387,411]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.575048" metricValueMax="9.144" metricValueMin="0.006096" pageId="105" pageNumber="104" unit="ft" value="1501.0" valueMax="3000.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3000 ft.</quantity>
, Champion./ 
